    "body": "shorter version:\n\n``` rust\nfn main() {\n    let ref mut x = Box::new(42);\n    let ref y = x;\n    **x = 0; // error: cannot assign to `**x` because it is borrowed\n}\n```\n\nI believe this is intended.\n\nAs for your example, let's see the caller part:\n\n``` rust\nfn foo(v: &mut Broken) {\n    v.x = 42;\n    v.do_stuff(); // we don't use the return value here\n    // now where is the chance to destruct 42?\n}\n```\n\nSo if we don't reject the `self.x = 0;` line, we never have a chance to detect the leak.\nIn short, the `self.x = 0;` line break basic rule of ownership system.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
